description:
Dredd: That Extra Mile [1]

Mega-City One, 2137 AD. Home to 50 million citizens, and still recovering from the decimation of the Chaos Bug, this urban hell is situated along the east coast of post-apocalyptic North America, where crime is rampant, poverty is rife, and unemployment near universal. Only the zero-tolerance Judges — empowered to dispense instant justice — can stop total anarchy. Toughest of them all is JUDGE DREDD — he is the Law!

Defoe: The London Hanged [8]

1671. It is five years since London was devastated by the Great Fire, the inferno caused by a comet passing over the capital. But from the ashes rose the undead, hungry for the flesh of the living. Protecting the populace was former Leveller Titus DEFOE, who led an elite squad of zombie hunters called the Brethren of the Night. But having defeated the evil magician Faust, who was controlling the stenches, Defoe has retired from zombie-hunting and returned to his old profession as a sedan-chair carrier, living in domestic happiness with fellow reek-seeker Tomazine Scarlet, her son Sean, and their new baby...

Tharg's Terror Tales: Night Shifts [1]

Experience the terrifying side of Thrill-power with these one-off tales from beyond the shadowy veil of sanity. Whether they be ghostly goings-on that send shivers up the spine or guts-to-the-wall splatterfests that sear the retina, nothing is what it seems in these glimpses of a horrifying realm beyond our own. Sitting alone at night, upon hearing a noise in the next room, do you investigate? Who knows what may be waiting for you...

Brass Sun: Motor Head [8]

The Orrery is a life-size clockwork solar system, a clutch of planets orbiting a vast BRASS SUN via immense metal spars, its origin and purpose long since forgotten. But the once-unified collection of worlds has regressed into eccentric fiefdoms, and ice is encroaching on the outer planets as the sun is dying. Young Wren has been charged with finding the scattered parts of the key that will restart the sun, and together with engineer Septimus she is embarking on an epic journey. But with an aspect of The Orrery’s creator The Blind Watchmaker living in her head, there are many who want Wren for themselves...

Bad Company: First Casualties [8]

It has been a decade since mankind fought a vicious war against the alien species the Krool on the planet Ararat. Young Private Danny Franks was just a raw recruit until he was drafted into the ragtag guerrilla unit known as BAD COMPANY, commanded by the psychopathic Kano. The conflict ended when Ararat exploded, and much of Bad Company was killed or listed MIA — now, as Earth prepares to mark the ten-year anniversary, Franks and fellow ex-soldiers Thrax, Mad Tommy and Fly-Trap are living in a veterans’ compound, dosed on psyche-chem to keep the nightmares at bay...

Cover: Jake Lynch

  • Judge Dredd - That Extra Mile (Part 1) (Alec Worley - Karl Richardson)

description:
76 pages of Astounding Action-Packed Arachnid-Adventure! Only £3.50!

Spider-Verse epilogue! The Spider-Verse may be over but the arachnid-army still has one superior foe to face!

Plus, Spider-Man 2099 returns to his own time and finds a ‘Future Imperfect!’

Also, Spider-Woman confronts her Loomworld counterpart… but why?!!

By Dan Slott, Guiseppe Camuncoli, Peter David, Will Sliney, Dennis Hopeless and Greg Land!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #15, Spider-Man 2099 #9 and Spider-Woman #4.

The saga of Atalante and the Argonauts, more epic than ever! The quest for the Golden Fleece continues!

After their escape from Hell, Atalanta and her companions are welcomed by King Aeëtes and his charming daughter, Medea, who interests Jason. And yet our heroes are searching for another treasure: the

fabulous Golden Fleece! But the Argonauts have to face several trials before reaching the object of their quest, including the terrible Colchis Bulls.
name: Les Taureaux de Colchide

description:
We are all blondes in our deepest hearts!

A new avalanche of gags for Vanessa and her friends!

The Blondes are dumber than ever!
name: C'est tous les jours Noël !

description:
There’s a body with a familiar face on an icy slab in the morgue: it’s Dylan Dog’s!

As not per usual, there is a huge silence in Scotland Yard, when Inspector Bloch enters. Nobody can find the courage to tell him that Dylan has been found dead. Luckily, the body lying on an icy morgue table doesn’t belong to the Nightmare Investigator, though it had his documents. The discovery of that corpse is just the beginning of a story that will really take Dylan just one step away from death, segregated and tied to a bed in an obscure jail, with his mind populated by horrible allucinations.
name: Destinato alla terra

description:
Groucho left Dylan and joined the freak circus: let the show begin!

As it happens every year, when Fall comes, the Circus is back. Dylan hates the circus and is scared by the ominous “freaks” who are forced to perform to wring a laugh from their audience. But among them, there’s also Groucho, who left a couple of years before to thicken the ranks of the artists who are destined to roam endlessly, from a city to another. Just to see his friend again, the Nightmare Investigator has no choice but wait for the lights of the colorful tent to go on and for the show to begin. Why can’t he see Groucho, during the performance? Under which guise is he concealed?
name: I raminghi dell'autunno

description:
A paradoxical enigma, in between life and death!

Dylan Dog is poised between life and death. So he finds himself in Hell, to investigate a case that even the sulfurous egghead of the Other Side cannot solve. A dark presence sneaked in the infernal regions and, as strange as it may seem, it’s killing the dead, particularly tormenting the serial killer’s souls. To get permanently back to life, our Old Boy has to disentangle this paradoxical enigma.
name: La paga dell'Inferno

description:
The life of Dylan’s son is in danger, though nobody know where the offspring of the Nightmare Investigator came from...

Dylan Dog has a son, Johnny. All of a sudden, the kid goes into a state of prostration and falls severely ill. Nobody is able to understand, though, what’s his condition and the situation soon becomes a true ordeal… But where does Johnny come from? What’s the enigma behind these events? And what’s the connection with the disappearing of another young boy, Thomas Shore, who mysteriously vanished into thin air, all of a sudden, for his parents’ distress?
name: Il calvario

description:
A quiet town, Greenhaven, falls prey of a hallucinating terror!

When the screech owl soars in the sky and his sinister call spreads over Greenhaven, a few miles from London, hallucinating events spread terror in the streets of this quiet town. In a room of the Ammontillado Hotel, inundated by water, a man is attacked by two giant crocodiles… a swarm of poisonous snakes slides into a pub… a boutique becomes a deadly trap, when a group of mannequins with evil intentions come to life… But what has all this to do with Old Gertie, who everybody thinks is a maleficent witch?
name: Brucia, strega... brucia!

description:
Who will wield Ishtar, the mythical weapon that slays dragons? Here is the story of an axe that went through the hands of the greatest.

The story is not about a person but a weapon, a combat axe: Ishtar’s Reaper, forged from a metal transformed by the Dragon’s Veill… A mythical weapon, one of the first

three of the Order of Dragon Knights, a blade that cuts down both men and beasts. But will the tale of the feats of the Knights who have wielded it be enough to give the necessary courage to the new holders?
name: La Faucheuse d'Ishtar

description:
The Goblins go on holiday! Hilarious and bloody catastrophes in prospect!

Problem: how can one go away on holiday to laze around in the sun when the whole holiday budget has been spent on the perpetual rebuilding of the village?

Solution: by exchanging houses, of course!

And, since for our fierce Goblins each solution generates a new problem, maybe they should have made enquiries before exchanging their village with unknown persons…
name: Sable chaud et légionnaires

description:
Dredd: Terror Rising [2]

Mega-City One, 2137 AD. This vast urban hell on the east coast of post-apocalyptic North America is home to 50 million citizens. Crime is rampant, and the Judges are empowered to dispense summary justice. These lawmen are judge, jury and executioner, and toughest of all is Judge Dredd he is the Law! Now, in the wake of Chaos Day, the terror group Total War are back...

Demon Nic: Demon Nic [6]

UK, the present day. Demons have walked alongside mankind since the dawn of time, humanity waging war on their species. But now an uneasy peace exists between the two races, and the Church operates as a quasi-military outfit to ensure no demon steps out of line. Cursed with a soul, and an outcast from both sides, Nicodemus just wants a quiet life...

Storm Warning: The Relic [6]

Brit-Cit, 2137 AD. Much like its Mega-City counterpart, Brit-Cit Justice Department has its various departments, from Tek to plainclothes, Tactical to Psi-Division, and one of its more prickly operatives in the latter is Lillian Storm, a psychically powerful Judge with the ability to talk to the dead. Unfortunately, her abilities are just as much a curse as they are a talent...

Lawless: Between Badrock & A Hard Place [6]

Colonial Marshal Metta Lawson is appointed to the frontier township of Badrock, and immediately has her work cut out for her bringing order to the colony, where trouble comes in many forms, from droid to mutant to uplift. Will she be able to maintain order where other lawmen have failed?

FREE Graphic Novel: Tyranny Rex: Deus Ex Machina - Volume 1 [1]

ARTIST, MERCENARY AND LAST OF HER KIND, THE SAURON TYRANNY REX HAS turned her back on her gun-slinging past and retreated to a convent on Corvakesh. But she and her fellow sisters are besieged by a ruthless and terrifying enemy, determined to get his hands on the GodSkin...

Cover: Colin MacNeil

  • Judge Dredd - Terror Rising (Part Two) (John Wagner - Colin Macneil)

description: Chassé-Croisé left billionaire Largo Winch wondering about his new love interest, Saïdée, a triple agent now held by the CIA. A bomb is set to explode during the company presidents' board meeting and that could be it for Largo and his group. But if Saïdée managed to escape and listened to her feelings, perhaps...
name: 20 secondes

description:
What mysterious object are the Nazis hiding in the icecap of the Arctic? A fantasy series that highlights aviation!

Whilst the first U-boats are discretely bringing from Argentina materials to rebuild the base of New-Swabia, Murnau and his companions discover, a thousand metres under the ice, the real origin of Thor’s Thunder.

At the other end of the world, in the heart of the Reich, Himmler starts to think that his time is really up…
name: La Foudre de Thor
